The Spirit, ſaith Salomon, returneth to God that gave it.

Her laſt words were, not much unlike that of S. Stevens here; Sweet Ieſus, helpe me: And, with the Spouſe in the Apocalypſe; 
               Apoc. 22. 20. 
               Come, Lord Ieſus, even now. With which words her ſpeech failing, yet ceaſed ſhe not, ſo long as any uſe of ſenſe continued, to lift up inceſſantly both hands, while abilitie ſo to doe laſted; and the one of them ſtill, when the other of them failed; thereby giving notice of her heart inwardly lift up unto him, who by his gracious hand at length tooke her hence, and received her to himſelfe.
